description:
&lt;p&gt;The PACU, post anaesthetic care unit, is an 8 bedded area at the Royal Free Hospital site which is currently under construction and due to open in December 2020. PACU is linked with recovery and high dependency unit on the third floor at the Royal Free site. It will focus on caring for those patients who are described as requiring level 1 to 1.5 level of care where a higher level of observation, monitoring and interventions can be provided post operatively. Our vision is simple, to provide a gold standard in peri-operative practice, and invest in you the people who deliver care. We are seeking enthusiastic and committed individuals to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to work in this new area and we are looking for a Band 5 registered Nurses with 6 months surgical, medical or recovery nursing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be a good communicator and able to work as part of a team and on their own initiative. Be willing to undertake specialist training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are number of benefits available in the Trust including Internal Transfer Scheme, access to accredited courses and staff accommodation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to know more about the Ward and PACU rotation then please do contact Senior Matron Mohammad Noor:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: mohammad.noor@nhs.net or bleep 1566&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recovery Team Leader - Jerwin Dispo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: jerwin.dispo@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
